      <h6 class="team-subheader">Adjunct Assistant Professor</h6>
      <p><%= image_tag("alessandro.jpg", :class => "team-thumbnail")%>
        My main research interest is to move from genes to function, in order to understand how genetic variability mechanistically leads to an increased risk of developing multiple sclerosis (MS). Additionally, I have
        been using genomic tools and mouse genetics to understand MS pathophysiology.<br><a href="mailto:alessandro.didonna@ucsf.edu">contact: alessandro.didonna@ucsf.edu</a>
      </p>
